Numerical Differentiation Using Excel
Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of numerical differentiation methods using Microsoft Excel to approximate the first derivative of the function:
\[f(x)=x-e^x\]
The numerical results are compared with the analytical derivative to evaluate the accuracy of each finite difference method through absolute error analysis.

Objectives
- Implement numerical differentiation methods in Microsoft Excel.
- Compare numerical results with the analytical derivative.
- Evaluate the accuracy of each method using absolute error.
- Visualize the function and numerical results using Excel charts.

Tools
- Microsoft Excel

Function
\[f(x)=x-e^x\]

Analytical derivative:
\[f'(x)=1-e^x\]

Numerical Methods
- Forward Difference (First Order)
- Backward Difference (First Order)
- Central Difference (Second Order)
- Second-Order Forward Difference
- Fourth-Order Central Difference

Analysis
This project includes:
- Numerical differentiation
- Analytical derivative comparison
- Absolute error calculation
- Data visualization using Excel charts

